cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about semantic image segmentation using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel layer for the network, which involves optimization of pixelwise affinity and semantic segmentation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves matrix multiplication, which could suggest it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
